{"title": "God of All Comfort", "description": "This book is written to Christians who profess to believe the Bible as God's revelation, but whose \"lives are filled with discomfort and unrest.\" Smith aims to show that the Bible's claim that God is the \"the God of all comfort\" is not an over-advertisement or misunderstanding, but that it is possible to avail ourselves of the doubts and heavy anxieties that plague so many Christians. <br/><br/>\n\nBy explaining God's part and man's part, Smith aims to show her readers that it is possible to overcome feelings of defeat and despair and find rest and peace in Christ. Abundant life and genuine enduring joy are available to all believers - even you. Deep and lasting peace, beyond all Earthly circumstances, is possible. \n\n(Introduction by Rachel Craig)", "duration": 29080, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2385", "name": "Hannah Whitall Smith"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt29/God_All_Comfort_1302.jpg", "copyright_year": "1906", "genres": ["*Non-fiction", "Self-Help", "Christianity - Other"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Megan Kunkel"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "TriciaG"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "01 - Why this book has been written", "readers": [6016], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/god_comfort_1110_librivox/godofallcomfort_01_smith_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1155}, {"section": 2, "title": "02 - What is his name?", "readers": [5809], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/god_comfort_1110_librivox/godofallcomfort_02_smith_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1719}, {"section": 3, "title": "03 - The God of all comfort", "readers": [5868], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/god_comfort_1110_librivox/godofallcomfort_03_smith_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1957}, {"section": 4, "title": "04 - The Lord our Shepherd", "readers": [6032], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/god_comfo